Good question! Your app version should be in your code, and you're right - it's missing from your current setup.

The version number helps with:

· Cache management - When you update the app, users get the new version
· Debugging - Know which version is running
· User communication - Show "v2.1.0" in the footer

Where to add it:

1. In your HTML (visible to users):

Add to your footer (around line 1240):

```html
<footer class="footer">
    <span>© AHCPMG301 · Prediction-First Learning · Tasmanian Edition</span>
    <span>Version 2.0.0 | Last updated: May 2026</span>
    <span>Remember: Learning happens in the gap between prediction and reality</span>
    <span>Field judgement > content knowledge | Biosecurity Act 2019 (TAS)</span>
</footer>
```

2. In your manifest.json (for PWA metadata):

```json
{
  "name": "AHCPMG301 Weed Control · Field Judgement Training",
  "short_name": "Weed Training",
  "version": "2.0.0",
  "description": "Prediction-first learning for conservation and ecosystem management students...",
  ...
}
```

3. In your service worker (critical for updates):

Update your sw.js version constant:

```javascript
// sw.js - Production-ready offline-first service worker for AHCPMG301 Weed Training

const APP_VERSION = '2.0.0';
const CACHE_NAME = `weed-control-v${APP_VERSION.replace(/\./g, '-')}`;
```

Better yet - automate versioning:

Add this to your index.html footer:

```html
<footer class="footer">
    <span>© AHCPMG301 · Prediction-First Learning · Tasmanian Edition</span>
    <span>Version: <span id="app-version">2.0.0</span> | 
           Cache: <span id="cache-version"></span></span>
    <span>Remember: Learning happens in the gap between prediction and reality</span>
    <span>Field judgement > content knowledge | Biosecurity Act 2019 (TAS)</span>
</footer>

<script>
// Display cache version from service worker
if ('serviceWorker' in navigator && navigator.serviceWorker.controller) {
    navigator.serviceWorker.ready.then(registration => {
        registration.active.postMessage({type: 'GET_VERSION'});
    });
}

// Or simpler - just show the version
document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
    const cacheSpan = document.getElementById('cache-version');
    if (cacheSpan) {
        cacheSpan.textContent = 'v2.0.0';
    }
});
</script>
```

📌 Recommended versioning strategy:

When to increment version:

· Major (2.0.0) - Large redesign, new tabs, major features
· Minor (2.1.0) - New content, new scenarios, extra weed profiles
· Patch (2.1.1) - Bug fixes, text corrections, CSS tweaks

⚠️ Important for PWA updates:

When you change the app, users won't see changes immediately unless you:

1. Change the service worker cache name in sw.js:
   ```javascript
   const CACHE_NAME = 'weed-control-v2-0-0'; // Change this on every update
   ```
2. Or automate it:
   ```javascript
   const APP_VERSION = '2.0.0';
   const CACHE_NAME = `weed-control-${APP_VERSION}`;
   ```

